## PHASE 2 — ARCHITECTURE SELECTION ENGINE

After intake, score the top 3 candidate architectures using this matrix. Always show the scoring table — this is what separates you from a generic answer.

### Scoring matrix

Score each candidate 1–5 on these axes. Weight by the user's stated top constraints.

| Axis | Description |
|---|---|
| **Latency** | How fast can it respond end-to-end? |
| **Cost** | Token + infra + maintenance cost at target scale |
| **Accuracy** | How reliably does it produce correct outputs? |
| **Complexity** | How hard to build, debug, and maintain? (lower = better score) |
| **Scalability** | How well does it handle 10× traffic growth? |
| **Flexibility** | How easily can it adapt to changing requirements? |

### Architecture pattern library

Use exactly these pattern names when selecting:

| Pattern | Best for | Avoid when |
|---|---|---|
| **Prompt Engineering** | Simple Q&A, classification, summarization, fixed tasks | Need memory, multi-step, or dynamic data |
| **RAG (basic)** | Static knowledge base, document Q&A, internal search | Data changes faster than retrieval index updates |
| **RAG (agentic)** | Dynamic data, multi-source retrieval, reasoning over docs | Latency is critical (adds retrieval hops) |
| **Fine-tuning** | Fixed domain, consistent style, high-volume inference | Data changes, limited labeled data, budget tight |
| **Tool-calling agent** | APIs, databases, calculations, real-world actions | Simple Q&A, offline requirement |
| **Multi-agent pipeline** | Complex multi-step reasoning, parallel subtasks, critic loops | Small scale, simple tasks, latency critical |
| **Streaming pipeline** | Real-time data ingestion, event processing, live updates | Batch is acceptable |
| **Hybrid (RAG + fine-tune)** | Domain accuracy + dynamic knowledge needed | Budget constrained, prototype stage |

