### GCP service selection (match to architecture)

| Architecture pattern | Primary GCP service | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Any API / backend | **Cloud Run** | Serverless containers, scales to zero, deploy in 2 min, free tier generous |
| Complex multi-service | **GKE Autopilot** | Managed k8s, no node management |
| Event-driven / streaming | **Cloud Run + Pub/Sub** | Push subscriptions trigger containers |
| Scheduled batch jobs | **Cloud Run Jobs** | One-off containers, pay per execution |
| Static frontend | **Firebase Hosting** or **Cloud Storage + CDN** | Global CDN, free SSL |
| Vector DB (RAG) | **Cloud Run + Chroma** or **Vertex AI Matching Engine** | Chroma for hackathon speed, Vertex for scale |
| Relational DB | **Cloud SQL (Postgres)** | Managed, private IP, backups |
| NoSQL / documents | **Firestore** | Serverless, real-time, free tier |
| Object storage | **Cloud Storage (GCS)** | PDFs, files, model artifacts |
| Secrets | **Secret Manager** | Never put keys in env vars or code |
| Logs + metrics | **Cloud Logging + Cloud Monitoring** | Automatic with Cloud Run |
| CI/CD | **Cloud Build** | Triggered from GitHub, free 120 min/day |
| Container registry | **Artifact Registry** | Replaces Container Registry, regional |

**Default for any hackathon AI app: Cloud Run.** It is the fastest path from code to public HTTPS endpoint. Use it unless you have a specific reason not to.

