### GCP deployment — step by step

#### 1. Project and auth setup
```bash
# Set project (replace with real project ID from credentials)
export PROJECT_ID="your-project-id"
export REGION="us-central1"  # or closest to your users

gcloud config set project $PROJECT_ID
gcloud config set run/region $REGION

# Enable required APIs (run once)
gcloud services enable \
  run.googleapis.com \
  cloudbuild.googleapis.com \
  secretmanager.googleapis.com \
  artifactregistry.googleapis.com \
  sqladmin.googleapis.com
```

#### 2. Store secrets (never use env vars for sensitive values)
```bash
# Store API keys in Secret Manager
echo -n "sk-ant-your-key" | gcloud secrets create ANTHROPIC_API_KEY \
  --data-file=- --replication-policy=automatic

# Grant Cloud Run access to secrets
gcloud secrets add-iam-policy-binding ANTHROPIC_API_KEY \
  --member="serviceAccount:$PROJECT_ID-compute@developer.gserviceaccount.com" \
  --role="roles/secretmanager.secretAccessor"
```

#### 3. Dockerfile (production-ready template)
```dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim

WORKDIR /app

# Install dependencies first (layer caching)
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

# Copy source
COPY . .

# Non-root user (security)
RUN useradd -m appuser && chown -R appuser /app
USER appuser

# Cloud Run requires PORT env var
ENV PORT=8080
EXPOSE 8080

CMD ["uvicorn", "main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8080"]
```

#### 4. Build and deploy to Cloud Run
```bash
# Option A: Direct deploy (Cloud Build handles the Docker build)
gcloud run deploy my-ai-app \
  --source . \
  --region $REGION \
  --allow-unauthenticated \
  --memory 2Gi \
  --cpu 2 \
  --concurrency 80 \
  --max-instances 10 \
  --set-secrets="ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=ANTHROPIC_API_KEY:latest" \
  --set-env-vars="ENVIRONMENT=production"

# Option B: Build image first, then deploy
gcloud builds submit --tag gcr.io/$PROJECT_ID/my-ai-app
gcloud run deploy my-ai-app \
  --image gcr.io/$PROJECT_ID/my-ai-app \
  --region $REGION \
  --allow-unauthenticated
```

#### 5. Verify deployment
```bash
# Get the live URL
gcloud run services describe my-ai-app \
  --region $REGION \
  --format="value(status.url)"

# Check logs immediately after deploy
gcloud logging read "resource.type=cloud_run_revision" \
  --limit=50 --format="table(timestamp,severity,textPayload)"
```

