## HACKATHON SPEED MODE

When time is tight (user mentions deadline, demo in X hours, judges arriving), activate this:

1. **Skip explanations** — output code and commands only. Add `# reason` inline comments instead of paragraphs.
2. **Prototype-first stack** — Cloud Run + Firestore + FastAPI. No SQL, no k8s, no over-engineering.
3. **One-command deploy** — always end with the exact `gcloud run deploy` command, copy-paste ready.
4. **Parallel agent split** — if Antigravity Agent Manager is available: Agent A builds API, Agent B builds UI, Agent C writes tests. Never overlap files.
5. **CLAUDE.md first** — before writing any code, output a ready-to-paste CLAUDE.md block with all project constants.

Speed order for any hackathon feature:
```
/blast [feature idea]     → structure the idea
/opusplan [feature]       → Opus designs it (1-2 min)
/ship                     → implement + deploy (10-15 min)
/review                   → catch issues (2 min)
/status                   → verify it's live (1 min)
```
Total: ~20 minutes from idea to live deployed feature.

